Durga Puja in West Bengal is the grandest and most culturally vibrant festival, celebrated with immense devotion and artistic brilliance. Marking the victory of Goddess Durga over the demon Mahishasura, it usually takes place in the autumn month of Ashwin and lasts for several days. During this time, beautifully crafted idols of the goddess are installed in elaborately decorated pandals across cities and villages, especially in Kolkata, which becomes the heart of the celebrations. The festival is not just religious but also a social and cultural extravaganza, featuring music, dance, food, and community gatherings. People dress in new clothes, visit pandals (known as “pandal hopping”), and enjoy traditional Bengali cuisine. The final day, known as Vijaya Dashami, concludes with emotional farewells as idols are immersed in rivers, symbolizing the goddess’s return to her heavenly abode.</p>
